==English==

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|bounc|ing}}

# To change the direction of motion after hitting an obstacle.
# To move quickly up and then down, or vice versa, once or repeatedly.
# ''colloquial:'' Of a [[cheque]]/[[check]], to be refused by a bank because it is drawn on insufficient funds.
# ''slang, AAVE:'' To [[leave]].
# ''slang, AAVE:'' To have [[sexual intercourse]].

====Synonyms====
*(''change direction of motion after hitting an obstacle''): [[bounce back]], [[rebound]]
*(''move quickly up and down''): [[bob]]

